briefdescription.para: Set QoS Queue Configuration - involves adding a new queue or modifying an existing queue, or deleting an existing queue.

parameterdescription.para: Name of interface on which queue is to be added (egress or ingress)
Queue configuration to add, modify or delete

Specifies if Filter is to do one of the following:
QOS_OP_F_ADD

listitem.para:
QOS_Q_F_QUEUE_SHAPER_DELETE
QueueId on successful / -1 on failure

briefdescription.para: Get one of all QoS Queue Configuration on given interface.

parameterdescription.para: Name of interface on which queue is to be queried (egress or ingress)
Name of queue which is to be queried
Number of queues returned
Array of Queue configuration of num_queues number of queues Caller must free the buffer

Specifies if the Filter is to do one of the following:
QOS_OP_F_INGRESS - if ingress queues are to be retrieved, otherwise egress queues are retrieved

simplesect.para: if QueueId is -1, then all queues for if_name are returned (number of queues given by num_queues), else only queue given by queue_id is returned

briefdescription.para: Get statistics of one or all Queues on given interface.

parameterdescription.para: Name of interface on which queue is to be queried (egress or ingress)
Name of queue for which statistics are to be queried
Number of queues returned
Array of Queue statistics of num_queues number of queues Caller must free the buffer
Specifies whether Filter is to do one of the following: QOS_OP_F_INGRESS - if ingress queues statistics are to be retrieved, otherwise egress queues statistics are retrieved

simplesect.para: if queue_name is not specified or NULL, then statistics of all queues for if_name are returned (number of queues given by num_queues), else only statistics of queue given by queue_name is returned
